{"key":"post-17016866","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17016866</id>\n<content>You're not supposed to add the agar to the water as the result will be exactly as you experienced, clumping.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You're supposed to put the agar in the dry bottle, add a small amount of cold water and mix it in.&amp;nbsp; This will make a paste.&amp;nbsp; Now you can add the rest of the water and mix without clumping.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17016959</next>\n<prev>17016840</prev>\n<first>17016653</first>\n<last>17016959</last>\n<when>1350043630</when>\n<utime>10/12/12 03:07 PM</utime>\n</post>"}